        <h3 class="project-title">
          3D Room Structure Reconstruction using Monocular Camera
        </h3>
        In recent years, with the spread of VR devices and technological improvements,
        the demand for technology that reflects real space in virtual space has increased.
        In particular, technology that reflects indoor environments in virtual space
        is used in various fields such as architecture, interior design, and robotics.
        To reflect real space in virtual space, it is necessary to estimate the 3D
        structure of real space, but expensive equipment is required, and there are
        problems in terms of computational complexity and ease of measurement. Therefore,
        in this research, we limit the estimation target to indoor environments and
        propose a 3D structure estimation method using a single image.
      </div>
    </div>

